    {
      "id": "46bcae32_4ef738ae",
      "file_path": "pom.xml",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 29,
      "message": "Initially the idea was to upgrade ccsdk version used in policy and make it clean by using dependency management in pom parent.\n\nWhile doing this we faced a cds bug : https://jira.onap.org/browse/CCSDK-1795\n\nThen we choose to rollback the change for ccsdk upgrade using parent dependency management and to re-do after CCSDK-1795 is fixed. A Jira item needs to be created to keep track of this enhancement.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5658,
        "name": "Bruno Sakoto",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "bruno.sakoto@bell.ca",
        "username": "brusak"
      },
      "updated": "2019-10-04 12:44:57.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "1000ed05_e4f1b684",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "9050c71a_1d6932a1",
      "file_path": "models-interactions/model-impl/cds/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/cds/client/CdsProcessorGrpcClient.java",
      "patchset_number": 7,
      "line": 82,
      "message": "I think there are some gaps with the concurrency handling. I think potentially another thread could get in calling cleanInstance()  right here under line 82, and you'll end up returning null (although it seems that the intent of this method is always to return a non-null instance).   I don't think the use of AtomicReference to hold the client instance is sufficient precaution.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 477,
        "name": "Jorge Hernandez",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jorge.hernandez-herrero@att.com",
        "username": "jhh"
      },
      "updated": "2019-10-04 16:16:56.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "6c6e5537_5e586398",
      "file_path": "models-interactions/model-impl/cds/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/cds/client/CdsProcessorGrpcClient.java",
      "patchset_number": 7,
      "line": 89,
      "message": "same comment as above",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 477,
        "name": "Jorge Hernandez",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jorge.hernandez-herrero@att.com",
        "username": "jhh"
      },
      "updated": "2019-10-04 16:16:56.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "71c780e1_e1f2e51d",
      "file_path": "models-interactions/model-impl/cds/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/cds/client/CdsProcessorGrpcClient.java",
      "patchset_number": 7,
      "line": 82,
      "message": "no, it can't return null after this; once it has a value, it will always have that value, as it is never set back to null.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
      },
      "updated": "2019-10-04 16:21:21.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "9050c71a_1d6932a1",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "599660e7_4c6a963f",
      "file_path": "models-interactions/model-impl/cds/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/cds/client/CdsProcessorGrpcClient.java",
      "patchset_number": 7,
      "line": 82,
      "message": "Exact, once set the instance is not supposed to return back to null.\n\nClean instance method has package visibility and can not be called from outside. It is used in CdsProcessorGrpcClientTest.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5658,
        "name": "Bruno Sakoto",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "bruno.sakoto@bell.ca",
        "username": "brusak"
      },
      "updated": "2019-10-04 16:27:02.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "71c780e1_e1f2e51d",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "c185cc57_d0660644",
      "file_path": "models-interactions/model-impl/cds/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/cds/client/CdsProcessorGrpcClient.java",
      "patchset_number": 7,
      "line": 82,
      "message": "So you don't need 'synchronized' correct?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 57,
        "name": "Pamela Dragosh",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "pd1248@att.com",
        "username": "pdragosh"
      },
      "updated": "2019-10-04 17:50:16.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "599660e7_4c6a963f",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "a18f4404_51a4b2f2",
      "file_path": "models-interactions/model-impl/cds/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/cds/client/CdsProcessorGrpcClient.java",
      "patchset_number": 7,
      "line": 82,
      "message": "it's atomic - no need for synchronized",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
      },
      "updated": "2019-10-04 17:51:24.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "c185cc57_d0660644",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "2a356a36_341e9bd2",
      "file_path": "models-interactions/model-impl/cds/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/cds/client/CdsProcessorGrpcClient.java",
      "patchset_number": 7,
      "line": 82,
      "message": "Correct. There is a potential race condition at startup to instantiate the instance at the same time, but because of the AtomicReference we are protected if ever this happens. Also it could only be once at startup.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5658,
        "name": "Bruno Sakoto",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "bruno.sakoto@bell.ca",
        "username": "brusak"
      },
      "updated": "2019-10-04 18:01:51.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "c185cc57_d0660644",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "001ece3a_6198a635",
      "file_path": "models-interactions/model-impl/cds/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/cds/client/CdsProcessorGrpcClient.java",
      "patchset_number": 7,
      "line": 82,
      "message": "I'm concerned with this scenario:\n\nThread-1: line 80: if (instance.get() == null) {\nThread-1: line 81: instance.compareAndSet(null, new CdsProcessorGrpcClient(listener, props));\nThread-1: line 82: }\nThread-2: line 71: instance.set(null);      /* another thread running into cleanInstance */\nThread-1: line 83: return instance.get();  /* returns null */\n\n??",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 477,
        "name": "Jorge Hernandez",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jorge.hernandez-herrero@att.com",
        "username": "jhh"
      },
      "updated": "2019-10-04 19:16:59.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "2a356a36_341e9bd2",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "df6d0856_dfd13a43",
      "file_path": "models-interactions/model-impl/cds/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/cds/client/CdsProcessorGrpcClient.java",
      "patchset_number": 7,
      "line": 82,
      "message": "oh, got it.  I assumed that cleanInstance() is only used for junit testing - perhaps a comment should be added to it",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
      },
      "updated": "2019-10-04 19:58:11.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "001ece3a_6198a635",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "478a2500_698f0af3",
      "file_path": "models-interactions/model-impl/cds/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/cds/client/CdsProcessorGrpcClient.java",
      "patchset_number": 7,
      "line": 82,
      "message": "Yes, as mentionned cleanInstance() visibility is package and is not available for public call. (to be added to documentation)\n\nBut we were reviewing the design with Rashmi and we agreeded to remove the singleton to have the client instantiated for every request. This to respond to the concern of registering the listener only once, the first time.\n\nIf performance optimization is later required, then we'll be able to see how to implement a pool of grpc client instances.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5658,
        "name": "Bruno Sakoto",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "bruno.sakoto@bell.ca",
        "username": "brusak"
      },
      "updated": "2019-10-04 20:12:10.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "df6d0856_dfd13a43",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
